Mini Project: Simple Order Matching Engine (C++17)

This is exactly the kind of logic used in trading systems, just simplified.

What You Will Build

A console-based engine that:
    Accepts BUY / SELL orders
    Matches them based on:
        Price priority
        Time priority
    Prints executed trades

Concepts Covered
    STL (priority_queue, vector)
    Custom comparator (important!)
    Basic system design thinking
    Real-world trading logic

Why This Project Matters
This small project shows:
    You understand order matching (core trading concept)
    You can use STL efficiently
    You think in systems, not just syntax

Next Upgrade (Very Important)
If you want to impress recruiters, extend it:
    Add order cancellation
    Add order IDs lookup (unordered_map)
    Add multi-threading (producer-consumer)
    Measure latency using chrono
    Use lock-free queue (advanced)